d","id":"10001","statusCategory":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/statuscategory/2","id":2,"key":"new","colorName":"blue-gray","name":"To Do"}},"components":[{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/component/10501","id":"10501","name":"Packaging"}],"timeoriginalestimate":null,"description":"The \"configure\" script file at the top level of the \"eucalyptus\" repository requires a long list of command-line parameters. The script sets up the Makedefs for subsequent \"make\" commands to use. Developers run this script before running \"make\". It only needs to be re-run if something changes about the dev env, such as Java 7 --> 8.\r\n\r\nCurrently, a typical configure command looks like this: \r\n\r\n{noformat}\r\n./configure --with-axis2==/usr/share/java/axis2 \\\r\n--with-axis2c=/usr/lib64/axis2c --prefix=/ \\\r\n--with-apache2-module-dir=/usr/lib64/httpd/modules \\\r\n--with-db-home=/usr/pgsql-9.2 \\\r\n--with-wsdl2c-sh=/home/lthomas/code/internal/eucalyptus/devel/euca-WSDL2C.sh \\\r\n--enable-systemd\r\n{noformat}\r\n\r\nMost of those parameters have well-known defaults, but all those options are required on the command line, or the command fails. The configure script could use defaults and not require these options unless they differ from defaults. That would allow developers not to have to chase down these paths, or copy & paste an existing command line they find somewhere that may or may not be accurate (anymore). Then the configure command could be (ideally):\r\n{noformat}\r\n./configure\r\n{noformat}\r\n\r\nFor extra credit, the script could look for env vars that the user could set, to override defaults, as well as accepting cmd-line params.\r\n\r\nThis command is in our published INSTALL process (https://raw.githubusercontent.com/eucalyptus/eucalyptus/master/INSTALL ), so it would make that doc cleaner too, and remove the need to keep that piece of the doc up-to-date as the command-line options change.\r\n","customfield_13000":null,"customfield_13200":null,"customfield_11300":null,"customfield_11500":null,"timetracking":{},"customfield_10401":null,"customfield_10005":null,"customfield_10600":null,"customfield_12900":null,"aggregatetimeestimate":null,"attachment":[],"summary":"\"configure\" dev script should allow defaults and not require list of command-line parameters","creator":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/user?username=lincoln.thomas","name":"lincoln.thomas","key":"lincoln.thomas","accountId":"557058:f9364c00-87ee-4948-b657-bb8f8f2030ea","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/c21bba9797b880c34a5d772e6db4664f?s=48&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3FownerId%3Dlincoln.thomas%26avatarId%3D17800%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","24x24":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/c21bba9797b880c34a5d772e6db4664f?s=24&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dsmall%26ownerId%3Dlincoln.thomas%26avatarId%3D17800%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","16x16":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/c21bba9797b880c34a5d772e6db4664f?s=16&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dxsmall%26ownerId%3Dlincoln.thomas%26avatarId%3D17800%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","32x32":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/c21bba9797b880c34a5d772e6db4664f?s=32&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dmedium%26ownerId%3Dlincoln.thomas%26avatarId%3D17800%26noRedirect%3Dtrue"},"displayName":"Lincoln Thomas","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"subtasks":[],"reporter":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/user?username=lincoln.thomas","name":"lincoln.thomas","key":"lincoln.thomas","accountId":"557058:f9364c00-87ee-4948-b657-bb8f8f2030ea","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/c21bba9797b880c34a5d772e6db4664f?s=48&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3FownerId%3Dlincoln.thomas%26avatarId%3D17800%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","24x24":"https://avatar-cdn.atlas